"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994045","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-10-31","<p>In autumn 2017, the Voluntary and Economic Incentives working group held a call for evidence on measures to reduce littering of drinks containers and promote recycling. This included seeking evidence on the costs, benefits and impacts of deposit and reward and return schemes, and gave the food and beverage industry the opportunity to provide their views.</p><p> </p><p>Defra officials held a stakeholder workshop, including representatives from the food and beverage industry, in June this year to discuss early thinking on a deposit return scheme and seek their feedback.</p><p> </p><p>Defra Ministers and Officials continue to engage with stakeholders from the food and beverage industry on an individual basis to discuss issues related to introducing a deposit return scheme.</p><p> </p><p>The Government has confirmed that it will introduce a deposit return scheme in England, subject to consultation later this year. The upcoming consultation will allow a further opportunity for the food and beverage industry to inform the development of any deposit return scheme.</p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2018-10-31T15:11:59.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994045/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994045/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994045/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-10-24","Beverage Containers: Recycling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what discussions he has had with the food and beverage industry on the introduction of a deposit return scheme for drinks containers.","false","Biography information for Steve Double","St Austell and Newquay","Steve Double","183372"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994046","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-10-29","<p>To enable adequate supply of the adjuvanted trivalent flu vaccine to be available in 2018-19, deliveries have had to be phased. All general practices and pharmacies in the United Kingdom will have the delivery of their orders phased across three months; 40% in September, 20% in October and 40% in November. This is a specific arrangement for 2018-19 to allow effective supply of the vaccine.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-10-29T17:47:53.883Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994046/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994046/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994046/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-10-24","Influenza: Vaccination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what assessment he has made of the adequacy of supplies of the aTIV flu vaccine for people over 65 years of age.","false","Biography information for Bridget Phillipson","Houghton and Sunderland South","Bridget Phillipson","183373"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994047","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-11-01","<p>NHS Blood and Transplant is responsible for the collection of donated blood and the production of blood products for the National Health Service in England. Modern safety standards are rigorous, and our blood supply is now one of the safest in the world. A donation which falls short of our standards during testing will be discarded.</p><p> </p><p>The most recent safe supplies annual report can be found at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/safe-supplies-annual-review/safe-supplies-a-year-of-change" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/safe-supplies-annual-review/safe-supplies-a-year-of-change</a></p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2018-11-01T16:53:33.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994047/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994047/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994047/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-10-24","Blood: Contamination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what information his Department holds on the presence of pathogens in contaminated blood products.","false","Biography information for Ian Lavery","Wansbeck","Ian Lavery","183374"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994048","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-11-01","<p>An assessment of average life expectancy for people who received infected blood products has not been carried out.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2018-11-01T16:55:34.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994048/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994048/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994048/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-10-24","Blood: Contamination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, whether his Department has made an assessment of the average life expectancy of all sub-groups who were affected by contaminated blood products.","false","Biography information for Ian Lavery","Wansbeck","Ian Lavery","183375"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994049","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-10-29","<p><strong> </strong></p><p>The figures for asset sales provided by the London Legacy Development Corporation in July 2018 for PQ 168018 are still current. The Corporation does not hold a schedule for asset sales, and the Department has not discussed the development of one with them.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch","183377","2018-10-29T12:26:43.753Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994049/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994049/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994049/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-10-24","Olympic Games 2012","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what proportion of the assets at the Olympic Park have been sold; what revenue those sales have yielded; what further such sales of assets are planned; and whether a schedule for asset sales exists.","false","Biography information for Mr Steve Reed","Croydon North","Mr Steve Reed","183376"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994050","Home Office","false","2018-11-20","<p>Funding for the anti-knife crime community fund has been increased from £1 million to £1.5 million in 2018/19 and we are funding 68 local projects across England and Wales this year. These include projects in Lancashire, but not West Lancashire specifically. We are ensuring that the funding is used effectively, and Home Office officials are conducting a series of evaluation visits to projects in order to be satisfied about effective delivery.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-11-20T17:18:18.963Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994050/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994050/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994050/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-10-24","Knife Crime Community Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if he will make an assessment of the effectiveness of the funding provided by his Department's Anti-Knife Crime Community Fund in tackling recent increases in knife crime in (a) West Lancashire constituency and (b) England.","false","Biography information for Rosie Cooper","West Lancashire","Rosie Cooper","183311"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994051","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-10-29","<p><strong> </strong></p><p>The figures for asset sales provided by the London Legacy Development Corporation in July 2018 for PQ 168018 are still current. The Corporation does not hold a schedule for asset sales, and the Department has not discussed the development of one with them.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch","183376","2018-10-29T12:26:43.817Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994051/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994051/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994051/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-10-24","Olympic Games 2012","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, whether his Department has met with the (a) London Legacy Development Corporation and (b) Mayor of London to discuss the development of a written timetable and payment schedule for sales of assets at the Olympic Park.","false","Biography information for Mr Steve Reed","Croydon North","Mr Steve Reed","183377"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994052","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-11-01","<p>An assessment of the potential mental health impact on people who have received infected blood products has not been carried out. However, in addition to non-discretionary payments to beneficiaries, the England Infected Blood Support Scheme also offers additional, time-limited discretionary support, which can include payments for counselling.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2018-11-01T16:57:16.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994052/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994052/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994052/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-10-24","Blood: Contamination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, whether his Department has made an assessment of the potential effect of contaminated blood products on the mental health of people who received those products.","false","Biography information for Ian Lavery","Wansbeck","Ian Lavery","183378"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994053","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-10-29","<p>The Department is working with relevant bodies across health and education to monitor the effects of the healthcare funding reforms on all the professions affected.</p><p> </p><p>A preliminary Equality Analysis was published alongside the public consultation document on 7 April 2016. This document provided the assessment of the potential effect of the replacement of National Health Service bursaries by student loans for all the protected characteristics of the Public Sector Equality Duty (Section 149 of the Equality Act 2010).</p><p> </p><p>The Equality Analysis and the Government consultation can be found at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/changing-how-healthcare-education-is-funded" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/changing-how-healthcare-education-is-funded</a></p><p> </p><p>A revised version of the original Equality Analysis, was published in February 2018 to accompany the reforms to pre-registration postgraduate healthcare funding.</p><p> </p><p>The revised Equality Analysis can be found at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/680681/Equality_Analysis_healthcare_education_funding.pdf" target="_blank">https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/680681/Equality_Analysis_healthcare_education_funding.pdf</a></p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2018-10-29T17:17:19.48Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994053/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994053/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994053/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-10-24","Health Professions: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what assessment he has made of the diversity of students taking (a) pre-registration physiotherapy and (b) nursing, midwifery and other allied health courses since the NHS bursary reforms in 2017.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","183289"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994054","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-10-29","<p>There is significant work surrounding community rehabilitation, with leadership from a stroke programme board in March 2018, co-chaired by the NHS England National Medical Director, Professor Steve Powis and Juliet Bouverie, CEO of the Stroke Association. The Board is overseeing the development of a stroke plan, which will include a strong focus on rehabilitation.</p><p>A review of community performance reporting is also underway to help the National Health Service to understand variations in clinical rehabilitation across services and patient groups. This will support clinical commissioning groups to target improvement initiatives in rehabilitation services.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-10-29T17:41:30.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994054/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994054/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994054/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-10-24","Rehabilitation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that those Clinical Commissioning Groups which are not commissioning adequate multi-disciplinary community rehabilitation services change their practices.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","183290"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994055","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-10-29","<p>This information is not held centrally in the Department.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2018-10-29T15:55:00.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994055/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994055/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994055/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-10-24","Department of Health and Social Care: Health Professions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many Senior Civil Servant staff within his Department are registered with the (a) Nursing and Midwifery Council,  (b) Health and Care Professions Council, (c) General Medical Council and (d) other health care professional regulatory bodies.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","183291"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994056","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-10-29","<p>The information requested is as shown in the following table:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="2"><p>NHS England senior management team (defined as employees who report directly to the Chief Executive)</p></td><td colspan="2"><p>NHS Improvement executive team (defined as employees who report directly to the Chief Executive)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Nursing and Midwifery Council registrant</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>Nursing and Midwifery Council registrant</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>General Medical Council registrant</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>General Medical Council registrant</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Health and Care Professionals Council registrant</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>Health and Care Professionals Council registrant</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Registrants of other health care professional regulatory bodies</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>Registrants of other health care professional regulatory bodies</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2018-10-29T17:15:11.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994056/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994056/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994056/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-10-24","NHS: Managers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many members of (a) NHS England’s senior management team and (b) NHS Improvement’s executive team are (i) Nursing and Midwifery Council registrants, (ii) Health and Care Professions Council registrants, (iii) General Medical Council registrants and (iv) registrants of other health care professional regulatory bodies.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","183292"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994057","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-10-29","<p>The Department does not hold the information as requested.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2018-10-29T17:20:09.217Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994057/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994057/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994057/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-10-24","NHS: Directors","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many board members and directors of NHS trusts in England are (a) Nursing and Midwifery Council registrants, (b) Health and Care Professions Council registrants, (c) General Medical Council registrants and (d) registrants of other health care professional regulatory bodies.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","183293"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994058","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-11-01","<p>The Statutory Sick Pay (Medical Evidence) Regulations 1985 already allow for other forms of medical information to be used in place of a fit note as long as there is an agreement between employer and employee that the other option, which can include an Allied Health Professions Advisory Fitness for Work Report, is acceptable. The regulations do not however name a particular alternative as being the most suitable replacement.</p><p> </p><p>In November 2017, The Government Command paper “<em>Improving Lives: The Future of Work, Health and Disability” </em>committed to investigating the feasibility of using the AHP Advisory Fitness for Work Report for the purposes of Statutory Sick Pay (SSP). The Paper can be found here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/improving-lives-the-future-of-work-health-and-disability" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/improving-lives-the-future-of-work-health-and-disability</a></p><p> </p><p>A rapid review was held in February 2018 involving extensive work by the Royal College of Occupational Therapists (RCOT) with its fellow organisations under the Allied Health Professions Federation and the Joint Department for Health and Social Care and Department for Work and Pensions Work and Health Unit. Following this, the RCOT and Chartered Society of Physiotherapists released a statement advising their members that the Allied Health Professions report can be used to provide evidence for the purposes of SSP and encouraging them to increase their use of this document within their professional remits.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>The link to statement can be found here: <a href="https://www.rcot.co.uk/news/ahp-advisory-fitness-work-report-admissible-evidence-statutory-sick-pay" target="_blank">https://www.rcot.co.uk/news/ahp-advisory-fitness-work-report-admissible-evidence-statutory-sick-pay</a></p><p> </p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2018-11-01T17:48:49.34Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994058/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994058/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994058/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-10-24","Statutory Sick Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what plans she has in place to communicate to key stakeholders in Government and the public and private sectors the outcome of her rapid review of the Allied Health Professions Advisory Fitness for Work Report which clarified that the report can be used to provide medical evidence for the purpose of statutory sick pay.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","183294"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994059","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-10-29","<p>Claire Perry, Minister of State for Energy and Clean Growth at the Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy (BEIS), who attends cabinet and is responsible for climate change mitigation, attended the meeting.</p><p> </p><p>Working closely with BEIS, Defra is delivering greenhouse gas emission reductions within the agriculture, forestry and waste management sectors, as set out in the Clean Growth Strategy and the 25 Year Environment Plan.</p><p> </p><p>We are leading the world in our response to the IPCC report. The UK hosted the European launch of the IPCC’s report at the first ever Green Great Britain Week held between 15-19 October. Following the report we have commissioned the UK’s independent advisors, the Committee on Climate Change, for advice on the implications of the Paris Agreement for the UK’s long-term emission reduction target, including on setting a net zero target.</p><p> </p>","Macclesfield","David Rutley",,"2018-10-29T17:55:37.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994059/answer","Biography information for David Rutley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994059/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994059/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-10-24","Carbon Emissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, for what reason he did not attend the recent meeting of EU environment ministers in Luxembourg on cutting CO2 emissions; and what steps his Department is taking to reduce UK emissions following the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change's Special Report on 1.5 degrees.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","183233"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994060","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-11-01","<p>The Department does not currently hold any contracts with Capita.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2018-11-01T13:16:21.793Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994060/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994060/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994060/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-10-24","Department of Health and Social Care: Capita","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, which contracts awarded by his Department are operated by Capita.","false","Biography information for Christian Matheson","City of Chester","Christian Matheson","183379"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994061","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-11-01","<p>The Department for Work and Pensions has 4 live contracts operated by Capita.</p><p> </p><p>They are;</p><p> </p><p>Personal Independence Payment (PIP) Assessment Service Lot 2: Central England and Wales</p><p>Network Management Contact Centre</p><p>Jobseeker's Allowance New Claims Contact Centre Service</p><p>Improving Access to Psychological Therapies Employment Adviser Training</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2018-11-01T13:06:29.423Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994061/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994061/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994061/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-10-24","Department for Work and Pensions: Capita","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, which contracts awarded by her Department are operated by Capita.","false","Biography information for Christian Matheson","City of Chester","Christian Matheson","183380"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994062","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-10-31","<p>The Ministry of Defence has 81 current contracts with Capita and 49 contracts which have end dates in the past but which are still to receive final payments or be formally closed down on the system. The total value of these arrangements is £1.28 billion.</p><p>This analysis incorporates contracts with Capita subsidiaries including PageOne Communications and Trustmarque Solutions.</p><p>These contracts cover a range of services, including the Army Recruiting Partnering Project, the Defence Infrastructure Organisation Strategic Business Partner and the Higher Education Pathway contract.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2018-10-31T15:42:58.41Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994062/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994062/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994062/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-10-24","Ministry of Defence: Capita","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, which contracts awarded by his Department are operated by Capita.","false","Biography information for Christian Matheson","City of Chester","Christian Matheson","183381"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994063","Department for Education","false","2018-11-01","<p>The Department’s records confirm Capita currently has seven contracts as listed in Annex A attached.</p><p>Since January 2011, details of central Government contracts above the value of £10,000 are published on Contracts Finder. Contracts published prior to 26 February 2015 can be viewed at:</p><p><a href="https://data.gov.uk/data/contracts-finder-archive" target="_blank">https://data.gov.uk/data/contracts-finder-archive</a>.</p><p>Those published after 26 February 2015 can be viewed at:</p><p><a href="https://www.contractsfinder.service.gov.uk/Search" target="_blank">https://www.contractsfinder.service.gov.uk/Search</a>.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2018-11-01T13:48:43.403Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994063/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994063/answer","183382_Annex_A_Table_of_contracts_operated_by_Capita.pdf","183382_Annex_A_Contracts_operated_by_Capita","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994063/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-10-24","Department for Education: Capita","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, which contracts awarded by his Department are operated by Capita.","false","Biography information for Christian Matheson","City of Chester","Christian Matheson","183382"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994064","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-11-01","<p>We centrally hold eleven contracts with Capita. These include the fire alarm upgrade works, the Diplomatic Academy learning space design and several Learning and Development courses.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2018-11-01T16:32:59.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994064/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994064/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994064/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-10-24","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Capita","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, which contracts awarded by his Department are operated by Capita.","false","Biography information for Christian Matheson","City of Chester","Christian Matheson","183383"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994065","Home Office","false","2018-11-01","<p>The Home Office currently holds 2 contracts with Capita, with a total contract value of £16.4m</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong><em>Title</em></strong></p></td><td><p><strong><em>Start Date</em></strong></p></td><td><p><strong><em>End Date</em></strong></p></td><td><p><strong><em>Value</em></strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><em>Electronic Monitoring Services</em></p></td><td><p><em>01/02/2014</em></p></td><td><p><em>31/03/2020</em></p></td><td><p><em>£16.0m</em></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><em>Immigration IT Test Analysis Services</em></p></td><td><p><em>01/11/2017</em></p></td><td><p><em>01/05/2019</em></p></td><td><p><em>£440,352</em></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The Home Office has since 2010, published details of its contracts over 10K on the Pan-Gov’t Contracts Finder portal, as part of the HMT Transparency Agenda. The link to the portal is as follows: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/contracts-finder" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/contracts-finder</a> .</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-11-01T16:49:26.65Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994065/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994065/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994065/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-10-24","Home Office: Capita","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department,  which contracts awarded by his Department are operated by Capita.","false","Biography information for Christian Matheson","City of Chester","Christian Matheson","183384"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994066","Department for International Development","false","2018-10-31","<p>The Department for International Development does not have any current centrally let contracts with Capita but does have some low value spend with Capita for FY 18/19.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-10-31T17:48:16.54Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994066/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994066/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/994066/answer",,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-10-24","Department for International Development: Capita","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, which contracts awarded by her Department are operated by Capita.","false","Biography information for Christian Matheson","City of Chester","Christian Matheson","183385"
